gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 135, Raptors 127
gameRecap.excerpt: The Thunder completed a 23-point comeback and defeated the Raptors, 135-127, in double overtime. Josh Giddey recorded 24 points, six rebounds, and six assists for the Thunder, with Shai Gilgeous-Alexander adding 23 points, a season-high 14 assists, and nine rebounds in the victory. The Thunder improve to 35-15, while the Raptors fall to 17-32.
